  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "Lumbini, the birthplace of Lord Buddha, a World Heritage Property, located in Western Nepal, and the landscape surrounding are of outstanding universal value. Two other sites included on Nepal's Tentative Lists, closely related to Lord Buddha's life, namely Ramagrama, the relic stupa of the Lord Buddha, and Tilaurakot, the archaeological remains of ancient Shakya Kingdom. Their safeguarding is important not only for Nepal, but for Buddhists worldwide. Therefore, this JFIT Lumbini project is designed to enable the national authorities to competently protect and manage the Lumbini World Heritage Property and to safeguard the cultural assets of Tilaurakot and Ramagrama."
    },
    "ne": null
  },
